simgui (0.5.20-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Gialersim blank card type support.
    Blank Fiskarheden cards are auto-detected as 'gialersim' type by pySim-read.
    Gialersim uses CHV 0x0C (not 0x0A), so standard VERIFY ADM1 fails with 6f00.
  * Add GIALERSIM to CardType enum with auto-detection from pySim-read output.
  * _run_pysim_prog uses '-t gialersim -a <ASCII_ADM1>' for gialersim cards
    instead of '-t auto -A <hex_ADM1>'.
  * authenticate() skips VERIFY for gialersim cards (ADM1 stored for pySim-prog).
  * _is_empty_card() treats gialersim as empty (full pySim-prog programming).
  * New _hex_to_adm1_ascii() helper for '-a' flag conversion.
  * Comprehensive tests: card type detection, hex conversion, routing.
  * 2044 tests pass.

 -- SimGUI Developers <simgui@example.com>  Tue, 17 Mar 2026 17:40:00 +0100

simgui (0.5.19-1) unstable; urgency=high

  * Blank card safety: skip VERIFY ADM1 on unpersonalised cards.
    Blank cards have no ADM1 set, so VERIFY consumes retry attempts uselessly.
    authenticate() now detects blank cards (empty _original_card_data or
    missing ICCID/IMSI) and stores ADM1 without sending VERIFY.
  * ADM1 format detection by length: 16 hex chars = hex format (Fiskarheden),
    ≤8 chars = ASCII format. Fixes incorrect conversion for different file formats.
  * Prevent reader contention causing 6f00 on VERIFY APDU.

 -- SimGUI Developers <simgui@example.com>  Mon, 17 Mar 2026 12:00:00 +0100

simgui (0.5.18-1) unstable; urgency=high

  * Detect pySim-shell APDU errors (SwMatchError/6f00) even on exit code 0.
    pySim-shell returns exit code 0 even when APDU commands fail internally.
    Output scanning now catches SwMatchError and 6f00 patterns.
  * Eliminate double ADM1 authentication during programming.
    _program_nonempty_card no longer sends verify_adm in piped commands
    since authentication is handled via the -A flag.
  * Program panel preserves card state on source change.
  * sudoers rule uses %sudo instead of %users.
  * check_sudo_mount uses file-existence instead of sudo probe.
  * docs: add TODO.md with test quality audit backlog.

 -- SimGUI Developers <simgui@example.com>  Mon, 16 Mar 2026 18:00:00 +0100

simgui (0.5.17-1) unstable; urgency=critical

  * CRITICAL FIX: Remove --noprompt from pySim-shell invocation.
    --noprompt prevented pySim-shell from reading piped stdin commands,
    causing verify_adm and all write operations to be silently ignored.
    This was the root cause of programming appearing to succeed while
    read-back verification correctly reported failure.
  * authenticate() via safe shell now correctly processes verify_adm.
  * _program_nonempty_card safe shell + piped commands now work.
  * Init-failure detection relies on output scanning (unchanged).
  * Updated tests: assert --noprompt is NOT present.

 -- SimGUI Developers <simgui@example.com>  Mon, 16 Mar 2026 14:00:00 +0100

